title: Tottenham Hotspur vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2024/2025
description: Tottenham won this exact fixture 2-1 last season, last winning consecutive home league games against Liverpool between 2008 and 2012. Liverpool have lost just two of their last 23 Premier League games against Tottenham and have scored at least once in each of their last 17 against Spurs.

title: Manchester City vs. Manchester United - English Premier League 2024/2025
description: Manchester City have won five of their last six Premier League games against Manchester United, more than they had in their previous 13. Manchester United have lost each of their last three Premier League away games against Man City, conceding 13 goals in the process. They last lost four consecutive league visits to the Citizens between 1952 and 1955.

title: UEFA Nations League .. Portugal The Champion
description: The 2024/25 season marked the fourth edition of the UEFA Nations League, with fierce competition between the top-tier teams, led by stars such as Mbappe, Dembele, Lamine Yamal, and Ronaldo. Defending champions Spain, who won the 2023 tournament, lost the final to Portugal 5-3 on penalties after a 2-2 draw after regulation and extra time. Portuguese star Ronaldo lifted the trophy once again.

title: Ruhr Valley – The Heart of German Football
description: Episode 6 then focuses on the season finale of the three big Ruhr Valley clubs in the 2024/25 season - with very different emotional worlds. In Bochum, the cameras follow VfL stadium announcer Michael Wurst around the emotional relegation of his favorite club, in Schalke the fans experience the end of the worst season in the clubs history and in Dortmund, stadium announcer Norbert Dickel hopes for the almost impossible: After finishing 10th in the first half of the season, BVB is hoping to secure a place in the Champions League with a win on the very last matchday.

title: LaLiga-LALIGA’S TOP SCORER 2024/2025
description: There’s been a riveting battle to become the top scorer of LALIGA EA SPORTS this season between two of the best strikers on the planet. In this feature we want to focus on the top scorer by looking back at all of his goals, highlighting his most exclusive stats from Mediacoach and listening to what he and his teammates have to say.

title: GP Confidential 2025 Magazine
description: Explore the sporting secrets of F1. Across 25 episodes and in crisp 3D animations, we analyses the technical details, which decide which teams make the most of the rules - and which need to go back to the drawing board. Complemented by features on historical milestones as well as race previews - GP Confidential is the perfect treat for any F1 fan.

title: DTM Show 2025-Zandvoort
description: DTM. The embodiment of Motorsport tradition. Having just turned 40, the DTM combines a unique fascination and familiarity with an unmistakable dynamic, signified by the rebranding with a new logo! Seven different manufacturers – ten different winners on six brands (Audi, BMW, Mercedes, Lamborghini, Porsche and Ferrari) through twelve races are but one testament to the unique competitive balance that makes every DTM weekend a revelation! And with the addition of Ford, the palette of different brands is only increasing!

title: Newcastle United vs Arsenal - English Premier League 2024/25 Week 10
description: Newcastle have won two of their last three Premier League home games against Arsenal, as many as they had in their previous 19 at St James’ Park against them combined. Arsenal lost this exact fixture 1-0 last season but haven’t lost consecutive away league games against Newcastle since their first three such visits in the Premier League between 1994 and 1996.

title: AFC Bournemouth vs Manchester City - English Premier League 2024/25 Week 10
description: Bournemouth have won none of their 20 league games against Man City. It’s the most one side has faced another without ever winning in English Football League history. Manchester City have won all 14 of their Premier League games against Bournemouth by an aggregate score of 45-7. It’s the best 100% record any team has against another in English top-flight history.

title: Man Utd vs Chelsea - Mini Match - English Premier League 2024/25
description: Man Utd vs Chelsea - Extended Highlights - English Premier League 2024/25

title: Wolverhampton Wanderers vs Crystal Palace - English Premier League 2024/25 Week 10
description: All six Premier League games between Wolves and Crystal Palace at Molineux have been won by a two-goal margin – Wolves’ three wins have all be 2-0, while the Eagles have won 2-0 twice and 3-1 once. Crystal Palace have won six of their last seven Premier League games against Wolves, as many wins as they’d managed in their previous 20 league matches against them.

title: Liverpool vs Brighton - English Premier League 2024/25 Week 10
description: After winning each of their first six Premier League games against Brighton, Liverpool have now won just two of their last eight. They did, however, win this exact fixture 2-1 last season. Brighton have taken five points from their last four away league games against Liverpool, more than they managed in their first 11 visits to Anfield.

title: UEFA Champions League 2024/25 - Best Goals of League Phase
description: The best goals from the league phase of UEFA Champions league for season 2024-2025.

title: Nottingham Forest vs West Ham United - English Premier League 2024/25 Week 10
description: Nottingham Forest have won both of their Premier League home games against West Ham since their return to the division in 2022. They last won more consecutively against the Hammers between 1969 and 1978. West Ham have lost two of their last four Premier League games against Nottingham Forest, having lost just one of their previous 15 against them in the top-flight.

title: Tottenham vs Aston Villa - English Premier League 2024/25 Week 10
description: Tottenham have lost three of their last four Premier League meetings with Aston Villa, though did win the last such match 4-0 in March. They’d only lost two of their previous 21 against the Villans. Aston Villa have won three of their last four Premier League away games against Tottenham, including the last two in a row under Unai Emery. They last won three consecutive away league games against Spurs between 1922 and 1924.

title: Ruhr Valley – The Heart of German Football
description: Episode 3 is about the heart-stopping final for the German championship in 2001, in which FC Schalke 04 thought they were German champions for four minutes before being overtaken by FC Bayern. The episode also looks at a similarly emotional day for S04s great rivals Borussia Dortmund: the dramatic loss of the 2023 championship on the final matchday, with BVB boss Hans-Joachim Watzke and former coach Edin Terzic, among others, giving an insight into their emotional lives.

title: Borussia Dortmund vs Mainz 05 - Bundesliga 2024/25 Week 27
description: 1. FSV Mainz 05 are unbeaten in their last four Bundesliga meetings with Borussia Dortmund, something they have only otherwise managed between 2005 and 2010. The start of this run was a 2-2 draw in Dortmund on matchday 34 in 2022/23, a result that cost BVB the league title. Mainz are on a two-game winning streak against Borussia for the first time in the Bundesliga, as many victories as they managed in their previous 18 top-flight match-ups combined. With 45 points after 26 games, 1. FSV Mainz 05 are enjoying their best-ever Bundesliga season and sit third in the table – the 05ers have never been in the top three this late into a top-flight campaign.

title: Holstein Kiel vs Werder Bremen - Bundesliga 2024/25 Week 27
description: Holstein Kiel are unbeaten in their two home games against SV Werder Bremen in professional football. Over the last 35 years, Werder have only won one of their 16 Bundesliga away games against league debutants : 2-1 at Union Berlin in September 2019. However, Bremen did get the better of the Storks in the reverse fixture, winning 2-1 at the Weserstadion. Holstein Kiel have lost 17 of their first ever 26 Bundesliga games – the last top-flight debutant to suffer as many defeats over their first 26 matches were St. Pauli in 1997/78, while only Saarbrucken in 1963/64 and Tasmania Berlin in 1965/66 have recorded more losses at this stage of a top-flight season.

title: Bundesliga - Special 2024/2025 Season Review I + II
description: A show that recap everything that happened throughout the 2024-2025 Bundesliga season. Well reflect on the most memorable moments from this incredible campaign and provide all of the matchday statistics.

title: Bayern Munchen vs St. Pauli - Bundesliga 2024/25 Week 27
description: FC Bayern Munchen have won eight of their last nine competitive games against FC St. Pauli, only losing to them during this period in February 2002. At home, Bayern have suffered just one defeat in eight matches against the Kiezkicker : 1-0 in March 1991 in the Bundesliga. FC Bayern Munchen are currently on a two-match winless run in the Bundesliga for just the second time under Vincent Kompany, having only previously happened in September/October. Bayern have dropped five points over the last two matchdays, as many as they let slip in their previous 12 fixtures combined.

title: Bayer Leverkusen vs Bochum - Bundesliga 2024/25 Week 27
description: VfL Bochum have lost each of their last four Bundesliga away games against Bayer 04 Leverkusen, failing to score in each of the last three. This is VfL’s longest ongoing losing streak away to any current top-flight team. With 56 points from 26 games, this is Bayer 04 Leverkusen’s second-best Bundesliga campaign. VfL Bochum, on the other hand, are enduring their second-worst top-flight season with 20 points and a goal difference of -25. The Werkself are six points adrift of first place – since three points for a win was introduced, only Stuttgart in 2006/07 have ever overturned such a deficit this late on in a Bundesliga season.

title: Ruhr Valley – The Heart of German Football
description: The first episode presents the Ruhr Valley as the “heart of German football” and focuses on the great rivalries - especially between Borussia Dortmund and Schalke 04. The main protagonists are the two 2014 German world champions Benedikt Howedes (Schalkes honorary captain) and Kevin GroSSkreutz (BVB legend). In addition to fans, Dortmunds club bosses Hans-Joachim Watzke and Lars Ricken, Schalkes coach of the century Huub Stevens, Bochums current coach Dieter Hecking, the two former coaches Edin Terzic (BVB) and Peter Neururer (Schalke and Bochum) as well as various former players share their emotional experiences.

title: Ruhr Valley – The Heart of German Football
description: Episode 4 then looks at the great era of Jurgen Klopp at Borussia Dortmund with the 2011 championship and the double win in 2012. The series also includes previously unreleased behind-the-scenes footage of the then BVB player Patrick Owomoyela and shows Klopps speech in the dressing room before the last game of 2010/11. The cameras also follow two of Schalkes almost 30,000 away fans around the second division away game in Berlin and Bochums cult coach Peter Neururer on a tour through the Ruhr valley on his Harley. The tour ends on the pitch of the Ruhrstadion, where Neururer performs his legendary dance routine from 2004 once again.

title: RB Leipzig vs Hoffenheim - Bundesliga 2024/25 Week 28
description: TSG Hoffenheim won 4-3 in the reverse fixture against RB Leipzig earlier this season and are now unbeaten in two Bundesliga games against them – TSG have never avoided defeat in three consecutive meetings with RBL. However, Hoffenheim are winless in their last six Bundesliga trips to Leipzig and have lost each of their last three away games against the Red Bulls. With 42 points after 27 games, this is currently RB Leipzig’s worst-ever Bundesliga season. Meanwhile, with 27 points and a -16 goal difference, this is TSG Hoffenheim’s second-worst record after 27 Bundesliga matchdays.

title: Bochum vs Stuttgart - Bundesliga 2024/25 Week 28
description: VfL Bochum have won just one of their last 15 Bundesliga games against VfB Stuttgart, although it was their most recent home meeting last season. VfB haven’t lost back-to-back top-flight matches away at Bochum since between 1995 and 1997. VfB Stuttgart haven’t lost any of their last 11 Bundesliga matches against teams sitting in the bottom three – it’s the joint longest ongoing run in the league together with champions Bayer 04 Leverkusen.

title: Ruhr Valley – The Heart of German Football
description: The second season of the ‘Bundesliga Original Series’ tells the story of a special region full of football passion. The series follows Dortmund, Bochum and Schalke through the second half of the 2024/25 season, but above all it portrays the Ruhr region as the epicentre of German football and shows the most emotional and greatest moments of the three clubs mentioned. For example, the series tells the stories of the European club titles in 1997, Schalkes near-championship in 2001, the Klopp era at Borussia Dortmund and Bochums historic fight against relegation in 2024

title: My Faith in Sport - Sawm
description: Ramadan is a crucial period in the Islamic calendar but fasting (Sawm) can provide complications for athletes who are trying to compete at the highest level. But to what extent is fasting a negative or can it actually aid performance? We look at the life and adaptation throughout Ramadan of Adam Azim – an unbeaten professional boxer from the UK, Fares El Bakh – a weightlifter who won Qatar’s first ever Olympic gold medal, and Zainab Alema – a rugby player who is aiming to become the first player to represent England wearing a hijab. Experts in Sports Science and Nutrition from Aspetar Clinic, Qatar also add detail of the physical impact athletes encounter during Ramadan.
